   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Fifty-nine THE WORD OF THE CROSS Scripture: 1 Cor 1:18-21 The meaning of the cross The cross is both the instrument by which the Lord Jesus died and the place where He died.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>By His death on the cross the Lord Jesus bore the sins of mankind and saved man from destruction.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Therefore, the cross is able to deliver man from sin and destruction.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The word of the cross The word of the cross includes the meaning of the cross and the teaching of the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Those who regard the meaning and the teaching of the cross as foolishness will perish.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Those who receive the word of the cross, recognizing that it is the power of God, will be saved.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The reason that the meaning and the teaching of the cross can cause man to be saved is that the cross is God s wisdom and power.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Wisdom is God s means; power is God s ability.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>God s means and ability to save man depend upon the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>How to apply the word of the cross Confess that we have sinned and deserve to perish.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Acknowledge that the cross is God s way of salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Accept Jesus Christ as the Savior who died on the cross to bear our sins.</S>
   </TEXT>
